rements, so templates might need to be changed to deploy resources. There are sample templates that can help bridge this gap.
Demo Day GuidanceAWS Tech U•https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/cfn-sample-templates.htmlAmazon CloudWatch collects monitoring and operational data in the form of logs, metrics, and events. It provides one view of AWS resources, applications and services that run on AWS, and on-premises servers.•https://aws.amazon.com/cloudwatch/You can transfer images to Amazon S3 via the internet, but you can also use AWS Direct Connect because we will use that for your other data. There is more information included in the user guide below.• https://docs.aws.amazon.com/directconnect/latest/UserGuide/dc-ug.pdfThese links above will serve as great resources for you. In addition, I wanted to include a link to the Well-Architected Framework that we discussed as a reference.If you have any additional questions or concerns, please reach out via email or phone! Thanks again,Sample 2Good afternoon <customer name>,Thank you again for taking the time to meet with <colleague name> and I this morning to review how AWS can help <customer organization name> meet its <customer organization goals>. When reviewing architectures such as yours, I always follow the AWS Well-Architected Framework as a guideline. If you would like to learn more about the AWS Well-Architected Framework, you can follow this link:https://aws.amazon.com/architecture/well-architected/Throughout our meeting, I noted several items that you would like to learn more about. I have included follow-up items for each of those questions and helpful links.1.I indicated in our meeting that there is an Amazon ECS Workshop that shows how to build out Amazon ECS and AWS CodePipeline quickly. Here is a link to that workshop:•https://ecsworkshop.com/2.You expressed an interest in learning more about AWS Simple Token Service (AWS STS). You can follow this link to learn more about it:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/STS/latest/APIReference/Welcome.html3.You wanted to take a deeper dive into AWS Certificate Manager. You